# Performance Audit Playbook

Structure: **Lighthouse categories + backend metrics.** Measure, compare against budgets, record deviations.

---

## When to run

- Pre-release (don't ship perf regressions)
- Pre-scaling (traffic growth expected)
- After major framework / library upgrade
- Cadence every N months on the critical paths

---

## Preparation

1. List critical user journeys (top 5–10 by traffic or revenue).
2. Define performance budgets if none exist:
   - LCP ≤ 2.5s (p75)
   - INP ≤ 200ms (p75)
   - CLS ≤ 0.1 (p75)
   - TTFB ≤ 600ms (p75)
   - API p95 ≤ defined per endpoint class (e.g., read <300ms, write <1s)
3. Access to: Lighthouse (CLI or web), real-user monitoring (RUM), APM, database query logs.
4. Staging environment that approximates prod.

---

## Frontend checks (Lighthouse + RUM)

### Core Web Vitals

- [ ] LCP within budget on p75 real users
- [ ] INP within budget
- [ ] CLS within budget
- [ ] TTFB within budget

### Loading performance

- [ ] JS bundle size reasonable (critical path <200KB gzipped)
- [ ] Images responsive + modern format (WebP/AVIF) + lazy-loaded below fold
- [ ] Fonts preloaded + `font-display: swap`
- [ ] Critical CSS inlined or first-paint blocks removed
- [ ] No render-blocking third-party scripts above fold

### Runtime performance

- [ ] Long tasks profiled; no >200ms tasks on interaction
- [ ] Virtualization on long lists
- [ ] Debounce/throttle on input-driven expensive operations
- [ ] Memory leaks absent on SPA navigation (heap stays stable)

---

## Backend checks

### Request handling

- [ ] p95 latency within budget per endpoint class
- [ ] No endpoints with >2s tail (p99) except documented long-running
- [ ] N+1 queries absent (ORM debug mode, query counts per request)
- [ ] Database query p95 acceptable (<100ms for hot paths)

### Caching

- [ ] HTTP cache headers correct on static assets
- [ ] CDN hit rate >80% on eligible assets
- [ ] App-level caching (Redis/memcached) for hot reads
- [ ] Cache invalidation strategy documented

### Background work

- [ ] Long operations moved to async queue
- [ ] Queue depth monitored, alerts configured
- [ ] Retry/backoff configured on external calls

### Database

- [ ] Slow query log reviewed; any query >500ms has an explain plan annotated
- [ ] Missing indices identified (via explain / query analyzer)
- [ ] Connection pool sized appropriately
- [ ] Replica lag acceptable if read replicas used

---

## Recording findings

Each budget breach or concern becomes a row in `../INVENTORY.md`:

```
| PERF-<AREA>-<N> | bug or risk | <area> | <metric> was <observed>, budget <target> | open | P<N> | {{DATE}} | {{DATE}} | {{DATE}} | — |
```

**Severity guide:**
- **P0** — breaks the product under current traffic (timeouts, OOMs)
- **P1** — breaches budget on hot path for many users
- **P2** — breaches budget on cold path or small user segment
- **P3** — theoretical future concern

---

## Output artifacts

- `index.md` — run context, scope (URLs/endpoints measured), device/network profile used
- `findings.md` — grouped by frontend vs backend
- Optional: `reports/lighthouse-<url>-<date>.html` — raw Lighthouse reports
- Optional: `reports/load-test-<scenario>.json` — load test outputs

---

## Tips

- **Measure on representative hardware.** Lighthouse on your M2 Pro doesn't reflect users.
- **p75 / p95, not averages.** Averages hide tail behavior.
- **Measure both synthetic and real.** Synthetic catches regressions; real catches what users actually feel.
- **Budget per page type.** Home ≠ dashboard ≠ checkout. Don't average budgets across them.
- **Track trends, not snapshots.** One-off measurements are noise; compare to last run.
